name: Ordinary Numbers
description:
Let's call a positive integer 
    n
 ordinary if in the decimal notation all
its digits are the same. For example, 
    1
, 
    2
 and 
    99
 are
ordinary numbers, but 
    719
 and 
    2021
 are not ordinary numbers. For a
given number 
    n
, find the number of ordinary numbers among the numbers
from 
    1
 to 
    n
. Input The first line contains one integer 
    t

(
    1 
    ≤ t 
    ≤ 10^4
). Then 
    t
 test cases follow. Each test case
is characterized by one integer 
    n
 (
    1 
    ≤ n 
    ≤ 10^9
). Output
For each test case output the number of ordinary numbers among numbers from

    1
 to 
    n
. Example Input 6 1 2 3 4 5 100 Output 1 2 3 4 5 18
